# Professional SaaS Landing Page Redesign

Redesign the landing page to look like a modern, lightweight SaaS product page — not an institute-specific page. Key goals: generate a hero image, use cyan-blue dominant theme (not purple), add a dynamic gallery in the "How It Transforms" section, add "Show More" for heavy content, and keep it lightweight.

## Proposed Changes

### Theme & Color Adjustments

#### [MODIFY] [Landing.css](file:///d:/Institute/institute1/src/app/Landing.css)
- Override `--human-secondary` from `var(--accent-secondary)` (purple `#8b5cf6`) → to a teal/emerald green `#06b6d4` so the landing page gradient stays in the cyan–teal family (no purple).
- Update `--gradient-human` to `linear-gradient(135deg, #0ea5e9, #06b6d4)` — a clean blue-to-teal SaaS gradient.
- Make nav background theme-aware using `var(--bg-primary)` with transparency instead of hardcoded `rgba(13, 14, 21, 0.8)`.
- Same for footer background.

