### Gallery Section — Dynamic + Manual (Replaces Heavy Infographics)

#### [NEW] [GallerySection.tsx](file:///d:/Institute/institute1/src/app/components/GallerySection.tsx)
A client component that:
1. Fetches gallery images dynamically from a `landing_gallery` Supabase table.
2. Falls back to manual/hardcoded items (the existing `student benifit.png` and `faculty and hod.png`).
3. Displays as a responsive grid (3 columns desktop, 2 tablet, 1 mobile).
4. Shows only **3 items initially** with a "**Show More**" button to reveal the rest — keeps the page lightweight.
5. Each card has a smooth border-radius, glass-card style, and hover zoom effect.

#### [NEW] Migration for `landing_gallery` table
A simple table: `id`, `image_url`, `title`, `description`, `sort_order`, `is_active`, `created_at`.
So admin can add images from the admin panel later.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The gallery DB migration creates a new `landing_gallery` table. This needs to be run on your Supabase instance. For now, the component will gracefully fallback to the existing manual images if the table doesn't exist yet.

